This helps confirm the solutions. - Using the recurrence relation \( f(x + 2) = f(x) + c + 1 \) derived from the functional equation, we find that the solutions must be linear. 5. **Conclusion**: - The only solutions are the constant function \( f(x) = -1 \) and the linear function \( f(x) = x + 1 \). Thus, the solutions are \(\boxed{f(x) = -1}\) and \(\boxed{f(x) = x + 1}\).
